{"build_type":"library","description":"Installs the kernel main thread's fixed arena AND arms the kernel memory pool (design section 2). Partitions the world arena: main thread gets a small slice [base+1024, base+(size>>6)) with g_arena_budget=main_slice (fixed=1); the rest [base+main_slice, base+size) is the KERNEL POOL. Writes the pool cursor cell (byte768=base+main_slice), pool end cell (byte776=base+size) and zeroes the memory-available doorbell (bytes808/816/824), initializes the worker seed (g_worker_arena_bytes=4MiB) and per-worker budget guard (g_worker_arena_budget=2GiB), then LAST writes g_kernel_pool_end=base+size to arm the door (allocate-system routes to the pool only once this is nonzero). Main thread is not clone-spawned; workers use endow. Also carves a ~192KiB lock-free reclaim-ring slab at the TOP of the world arena (pool end cell lowered to slab_base so the pool never grows into it), records the slab base in header cell base+832, writes the 3 size-class sizes (1MiB, seed+16, 8MiB-stack+16), and seeds each ring's per-slot sequence words. Single-threaded at boot, race-free.","module_name":"install-fixed-arena-before-entering-kernel","package_name":"install-fixed-arena-before-entering-kernel","function_definitions":{"install-fixed-arena-before-entering-kernel":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"envelope_ptr","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"unused","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i0","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"i1","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operati